# dxkit self-scan exclusions — applied when running dxkit against
# its OWN repo root (e.g. `vyuh-dxkit vulnerabilities .`). Does NOT
# apply when dxkit analyzes a fixture directory directly (different
# cwd → different exclusion set), so the cross-ecosystem integration
# tests under test/fixtures/benchmarks/ continue to surface the
# deliberate findings they assert on.

# Cross-ecosystem benchmark fixtures (Phase 10h.6.8 + 10i.0).
# These contain deliberately-vulnerable manifests, hardcoded fake
# secrets, lint violations, duplications, and untested files used by
# test/integration/cross-ecosystem.test.ts. They are NOT dxkit's own
# source — they are test artifacts. Excluding them prevents false
# positives in dxkit's self-health-check.
test/fixtures/benchmarks/
